title: RCPD Make Arrest In Convenience Store Robbery Case
text:
RCPD Make Arrest In Convenience Store Robbery Case October 11, 2015, 2:57 PM RAPID CITY, SD - 
A 22-year-old man has been arrested in Rapid City for a convenience store robbery last week. 
A Rapid City Police detective arrested Taylor Chapman Saturday night. Chapman was one of two suspects police were searching for following a robbery on October 4. 
Chapman was caught during a traffic stop and brought into custody for outstanding warrants. After being questioned about the robbery, he was later arrested. 
Chapman faces first degree robbery charges, among others. The other robbery suspect has not been found. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
